### 1.0.0

* Initial version transformed from the previous DS-KM GitHub repository up to [ds-km@8442837](https://github.com/ds-wizard/ds-km/commit/8442837dbe3ff899b09e7d8d3fc1107e935a876f)', 'Apache-2.0', 'dsw:root:2.3.0', null, null, '[{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":{"changed":true,"value":"We will make sure that we know what data will be coming together in the project, when it will be coming. We also need to make sure that we have adequate storage space to deal with it, and that all the responsibilities have been taken care of.\n\nSee also [Collecting in RDMKit](https://rdmkit.elixir-europe.org/collecting)"},"uuid":"d8e93d3f-741f-466e-b285-d1173d36bbf8","questionUuids":{"changed":false},"entityUuid":"b1df3c74-0b1f-4574-81c4-4cc2d780c1af","parentUuid":"6f6241d9-136c-4770-9d58-8a3f39607052","eventType":"EditChapterEvent","title":{"changed":false}},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":{"changed":true,"value":"In this chapter we describe all the sources of data: they can e.g. come from instruments or from questionnaires; data can be newly collected as part of the current project, but it can also be pre-existing data that may need proper contracts with the maintainer, some pre-processing, and quality checks. It can also be reference data that is part of curated resources and (public) databases. \n\nFor more information see [Collecting in RDMKit](https://rdmkit.elixir-europe.org/collecting)"},"uuid":"bf8fde5e-e357-4722-9822-ef72a26e7216","questionUuids":{"changed":false},"entityUuid":"b1df3c74-0b1f-4574-81c4-4cc2d780c1af","parentUuid":"6f6241d9-136c-4770-9d58-8a3f39607052","eventType":"EditChapterEvent","title":{"changed":false}},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"tagUuids":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":{"changed":true,"value":"Data analysis is normally done step-by-step.  It is important that for all data the origin and all processing and filtering steps are documented, otherwise results will not be reproducible. \n\nRe-users of the data also need this information to decide whether the data can be used for their purpose."},"uuid":"9c341560-a1cf-4e56-a600-813955ddcc02","expertUuids":{"changed":false},"entityUuid":"948b5fd8-c1bd-457d-8f81-ea2fd093f541","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","parentUuid":"6d18bfff-0f53-469b-934e-9806dda9d4fb","eventType":"EditQuestionEvent","answerUuids":{"changed":false},"referenceUuids":{"changed":false},"title":{"changed":false},"requiredPhaseUuid":{"changed":false}},{"annotations":{"changed":false},"tagUuids":{"changed":false},"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":{"changed":true,"value":"For the re-usability of your data by yourself or others at a later stage, a lot of information about the data --for example how it was collected and how it can be used-- should be stored with the data. Such *data about the data* is called **metadata**, and this set of questions are about this metadata."},"uuid":"840c2fc4-9424-4ea3-a067-f7bd7861f512","expertUuids":{"changed":false},"entityUuid":"8c962e6f-17ee-4b22-8ebb-9f06f779e3b3","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","parentUuid":"b1df3c74-0b1f-4574-81c4-4cc2d780c1af","eventType":"EditQuestionEvent","answerUuids":{"changed":false},"referenceUuids":{"changed":false},"title":{"changed":false},"requiredPhaseUuid":{"changed":false}},{"annotations":[],"tagUuids":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":"In the design of your experiment, there are many considerations and techniques that cab be used to ensure and monitor data quality.","uuid":"1b8e9ffe-fefe-4cd0-b3bd-99f7955e2bc1","entityUuid":"59cd7bb6-8b24-4a4b-9baa-e7147807c58d","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","parentUuid":"b1df3c74-0b1f-4574-81c4-4cc2d780c1af","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","title":"What techniques are you using to ensure data quality?","requiredPhaseUuid":null},{"annotations":[],"advice":null,"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","uuid":"3b5b3804-fee0-413c-809f-5805b6906075","entityUuid":"f55f2b65-40ea-428c-99e3-f78b9e8032a0","parentUuid":"59cd7bb6-8b24-4a4b-9baa-e7147807c58d","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","metricMeasures":[],"label":"Explore"},{"annotations":[],"tagUuids":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":null,"uuid":"539a33ca-d8c5-4a88-a7c1-ee9ce93e138c","entityUuid":"9a4050de-5264-4de6-933c-3cfff3684119","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","parentUuid":"f55f2b65-40ea-428c-99e3-f78b9e8032a0","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","title":"Will you be repeating experiments to monitor consistency of the results?","requiredPhaseUuid":null},{"annotations":[],"advice":null,"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","uuid":"2b83b4d6-4f6f-49cb-90c1-185e57442174","entityUuid":"33e6d62f-a1a8-4cee-ad93-dea427405722","parentUuid":"9a4050de-5264-4de6-933c-3cfff3684119","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","metricMeasures":[],"label":"No"},{"annotations":[],"advice":null,"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","uuid":"70610b9c-a94a-4cfe-989d-9be4876ab7c7","entityUuid":"faad6703-7c7a-43e7-9b38-33ea5fed66c2","parentUuid":"9a4050de-5264-4de6-933c-3cfff3684119","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","metricMeasures":[],"label":"Yes"},{"annotations":[],"tagUuids":[],"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","text":null,"uuid":"baf34381-6384-4ea7-aa8c-d4d746612809","entityUuid":"691f896d-c28f-4da8-b648-9dab7066d454","questionType":"OptionsQuestion","parentUuid":"f55f2b65-40ea-428c-99e3-f78b9e8032a0","eventType":"AddQuestionEvent","title":"Will you include experiments for which the outcome is known to monitor consistency of the results?","requiredPhaseUuid":null},{"annotations":[],"advice":null,"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","uuid":"7b25e7b7-8914-4426-a18e-7ac4a61aba7b","entityUuid":"40f366d2-57b8-4113-b597-ad2fd2376c0c","parentUuid":"691f896d-c28f-4da8-b648-9dab7066d454","eventType":"AddAnswerEvent","metricMeasures":[],"label":"No"},{"annotations":[],"advice":null,"createdAt":"2021-11-02T10:22:46.775632Z","uuid":"246dd1ba-7299-4fc5-ba2e-